prompt:
You are reviewing a Supabase migration for tenant isolation gaps before deploy. The data model is compound auth: each row belongs to ONE user WITHIN ONE org; a user may belong to multiple orgs (via a `org_members` table). Audit the policy posture and produce: (1) per-table posture table; (2) gaps with severity citing concrete failure modes (think carefully: surface-correct SQL may still leak); (3) migration-shaped remediation; (4) follow-the-data trace.

Migration file:

```sql
-- migrations/20260606140001_tasks_with_org_scope.sql
CREATE TABLE org_members (
  org_id uuid NOT NULL,
  user_id uuid NOT NULL,
  role text DEFAULT 'member',
  PRIMARY KEY (org_id, user_id)
);

ALTER TABLE org_members ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE org_members FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

CREATE POLICY org_members_select ON org_members
  FOR SELECT USING (user_id = auth.uid());

CREATE TABLE tasks (
  id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  org_id uuid NOT NULL,
  user_id uuid NOT NULL,
  title text NOT NULL,
  created_at timestamptz DEFAULT now()
);

ALTER TABLE tasks ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE tasks FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

CREATE POLICY tasks_user_select ON tasks
  FOR SELECT USING (user_id = auth.uid())
  WITH CHECK (user_id = auth.uid());

CREATE POLICY tasks_user_insert ON tasks
  FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (user_id = auth.uid());

CREATE POLICY tasks_user_update ON tasks
  FOR UPDATE USING (user_id = auth.uid()) WITH CHECK (user_id = auth.uid());

CREATE POLICY tasks_user_delete ON tasks
  FOR DELETE USING (user_id = auth.uid());
```

Auth model: `auth.uid()`. Tenant scope: COMPOUND -- per-org-per-user. Concrete data scenario: user U1 belongs to BOTH org A and org B; user U2 belongs to org B only. U1 creates tasks under (org_A, U1) and (org_B, U1). Question to drive the audit: can U1 ever leak a task across orgs through this policy set, and if so, how?
